In France, voting has traditionally been a little technical experience: voters isolate themselves in a cabin and insert a previously printed paper sheet into an envelope indicating which candidate they chose.
After officials check the voter's identity, he leaves the envelope in the ballot box and signs the voting list.
The French election law rather strictly codifies the procedures to follow.
